OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Mississippi River near East River Flats Park in Minneapolis
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The site is located just below East River Flats Park on the left bank in Minneapolis. It is approximately 210 degrees to the light pole on the right bank and 52 degrees to the double-boled tree upstream of the landing on the left bank.
HorizontalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Mississippi River near St. Paul Water Works Pumping Station
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The site is located near the boat launch at River Park in Brooklyn Park, next to the pumping station on the left bank. It is approximately 64 degrees to the post on the pumping stations balcony on the left bank and 263 degrees to the cottonwood with a split bole on the right bank.
HorizontalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Mississippi River upstream of the Coon Rapids Dam
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The site is located upstream of the Coon Rapids Dam. It is approximately 232 degrees to the tire on the dock in front of the brown and white house on the right bank and 64 degrees to the willow tree located in the 'divit' on the left bank.
HorizontalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Mississippi River just above the Crow River Confluence
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The site is located just above the Crow River confluence near Dayton. It is approximately 260 degrees to the most downstream sign on the island and 28 degrees to the light post upstream of the yellow house on the left bank.
HorizontalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Snake River Approx. 1/2 Mile Upstream of the St. Croix River
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is located mid-channel on the Snake River, about 1/2 of a mile upstream from where the Snake empties into the St. Croix River.  The nearest active USGS flow monitoring station is located near Pine City, Minnesota (USGS 05338500), which is 8 to 9 miles upstream of the water quality monitoring station.
HorizontalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: St. Croix River Just Upstream from Norway Point Boat Landing
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is located on the St. Croix River just upstream from the boat landing at Norway Point.  It is located mid-channel, just around the first bend in the river upstream of the boat landing.  The nearest active USGS flow monitoring station is located right at the boat landing for Norway Point (USGS 05336000).
HorizontalCollectionMethodName: GPS Code (Pseudo Range) Standard Position (SA Off)

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: St. Croix River near Osceola Landing
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The station is located on the St. Croix River approximately 1.4 miles downstream from Osceola Landing, mid-channel, adjacent to the campground at river mile S43.7.

MonitoringLocationName: CLOQUET R AT CSAH 7, 4.5 MI SW OF INDEPENDENCE, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS AT THE CLOQUET RIVER AT THE BRIDGE ON COUNTY STATE AID HIGHWAY 7, 4.1 MILES FROM ITS POINT OF DISCHARGE INTO THE ST. LOUIS RIVER AND 4.5 MILES SOUTHWEST OF INDEPENDENCE, MINNESOTA.  THE RIVER IS BASICALLY UNAFFECTED BY HUMAN DEVELOPMENT, MOSTLY NATURAL, WITH VERY LITTLE AGRICULTURAL INFLUENCE.

OrganizationFormalName: Minnesota Pollution Control Agency - Ambient Surface Water
MonitoringLocationName: ST. LOUIS R AT SH-33 BRG IN CLOQUET, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS AT THE ST. LOUIS RIVER AT BRIDGE AT STATE NUMBERED TRUNK HIGHWAY 33 CROSSING IN CLOQUET, MINNESOTA.  THE SAMPLES ARE TAKEN IN THE NORTH CHANNEL TO REPRESENT THE RIVER'S QUALITY IMMEDIATELY BEFORE THE INFLUENCE OF THE CLOQUET AREA.

OrganizationFormalName: Minnesota Pollution Control Agency - Ambient Surface Water
MonitoringLocationName: ST. LOUIS R. FOND DU LAC RESERVOIR AT DAM, 3.3 MI W GARY, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS AT THE ST. LOUIS RIVER AT THE FOND DU LAC RESERVOIR.  THIS POINT IS AFTER THE TWO CHANNELS MERGE AND FORM THE LAST RESERVOIR IN THE ST. LOUIS SYSTEM, 3.3 MILES WEST OF GARY, MINNESOTA.  SAMPLES HERE ARE COLLECTED AT THE DAM PRIOR TO THE HYDRO PLANT SPILLWAY.

OrganizationFormalName: Minnesota Pollution Control Agency - Ambient Surface Water
MonitoringLocationName: ST. LOUIS R AT DUNLAP BRG IN CLOQUET, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS AT THE ST. LOUIS RIVER IN THE SOUTH CHANNEL AS IT CROSSES THE DUNLAP ISLAND BRIDGE IN NORTH SIDE OF CLOQUET, MINNESOTA.  WATER IN THE SOUTH CHANNEL IS DIRECTLY INFLUENCED BY THE EFFLUENTS FROM THE CONWED CORPORATION.  BECAUSE OF BOTH ITS CLOSE PROXIMITY TO CONWED AND INCOMPLETE MIXING, THIS SAMPLING POINT WAS DISCONTINUED AND MOVED 0.2 OF A MILE DOWNSTREAM TO OBTAIN A MORE REPRESENTATIVE SAMPLE.

OrganizationFormalName: Minnesota Pollution Control Agency - Ambient Surface Water
MonitoringLocationName: ST. LOUIS R AT CSAH 31 IN BROOKSTON, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS AT THE ST. LOUIS RIVER AT THE COUNTY STATE AID HIGHWAY 31 AT THE BROOKSTON BRIDGE CROSSING AT THE NORTH SIDE OF BROOKSTON, MINNESOTA.  THIS IS THE UPPERMOST SAMPLE POINT ON THE ST. LOUIS RIVER THAT IS MONITORED IN OUR PROGRAM.  THE SAMPLE POINT IS ABOVE THE INFLUENCE OF THE CLOQUET, ARTICHOKE AND STONY BROOK RIVER TRIBUTARIES.

OrganizationFormalName: Minnesota Pollution Control Agency - Ambient Surface Water
MonitoringLocationName: UNNAMED TRIB AT FORBAY LK OUTLT, 2.3 MI E OF THOMSON, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS AT AN UNNAMED TRIBUTARY AT OUTLET FROM FORBAY LAKE AND AT THE FORBAY LAKE HYDRO-ELECTRIC PLANT.  THE SITE IS 2.3 MILES EAST OF THOMSON, MINNESOTA.  THE SAMPLES ARE COLLECTED AT THE UPPER GATE PRIOR TO DISCHARGING INTO THE HYDRO PLANT.  THE SAMPLE POINT WAS LOCATED TO NOTE THE WATER QUALITY CHANGES THAT MIGHT OCCUR AS THE WATERS HAVE LEFT THOMSON RESERVOIR AND THEN PONDED AGAIN IN FORBAY LAKE THROUGH THE NORTH CHANNEL.

OrganizationFormalName: Minnesota Pollution Control Agency - Ambient Surface Water
MonitoringLocationName: ST. LOUIS R AT BRG IN N CHANNEL, 1 MI SE OF DULUTH, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS THE ST. LOUIS RIVER AT THE SOO RAILROAD BRIDGE IN THE NORTH CHANNEL 1 MILE SOUTHEAST OF DULUTH, MINNESOTA.  THE SAMPLING POINT IS INFLUENCED BY THE DULUTH WASTE- WATER TREATMENT PLANT ALONG WITH ALL THE COMMERCIAL AND INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENTS IN THIS AREA.  THIS IS OUR LAST ACTIVE SAMPLING POINT.

OrganizationFormalName: Minnesota Pollution Control Agency - Ambient Surface Water
MonitoringLocationName: ST. LOUIS R AT ARROWHEAD BRIDGE, 0.7 MI SE OF DULUTH, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS THE ST. LOUIS RIVER AT THE ARROWHEAD BRIDGE AND 0.6 MILES SOUTH OF THE U.S. HIGHWAY 2 CROSSING AT THE BONG BRIDGE AND 0.7 MILES SOUTHEAST OF DULUTH, MINNESOTA.  INPUTS AFFECTING THE WATER QUALITIES HERE INCLUDE THE U.S. STEEL PLANT, GARY AND SMITHVILLE WASTEWATER TREATMENT PLANTS, SEVERAL CREEK DISCHARGES, AND THE PHYSICAL CHANGES THAT OCCUR IN THE RIVER ITSELF.

OrganizationFormalName: Minnesota Pollution Control Agency - Ambient Surface Water
MonitoringLocationName: UNNAMED TRIB OUTLT FROM THOMSON RES, .4 MI NE OF THOMSON, MN
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THIS STATION WAS ESTABLISHED BY THE WESTERN LAKE SUPERIOR SANITARY DISTRICT AS PART OF A ROUTINE WATER QUALITY MONITORING PROGRAM AND IS AN UNNAMED TRIBUTARY AS IT LEAVES THE THOMSON RESERVOIR AT THE EAST END DAM AND EVENTUALLY FLOWS INTO THE ST. LOUIS RIVER.  THIS SAMPLE POINT REPRESENTS THE CHANGES IN WATER QUALITIES AS INFLUENCED BY THE RESERVOIR AND THE INPUT BY THE MIDWAY RIVER.  THE MAJORITY OF THE RESERVOIR'S DISCHARGE ENTERS THIS NORTHERN-MOST CHANNEL.
